1
00:01:31,858 --> 00:01:33,018
Whoa!

2
00:01:42,691 --> 00:01:44,662
All the food's gonna go bad.

3
00:01:47,022 --> 00:01:48,682
Yeah, I drew up a list.

4
00:01:48,707 --> 00:01:51,972
I'll hit the store
before it gets all bought out.

5
00:01:54,214 --> 00:01:55,203
Fuck.

6
00:01:55,507 --> 00:01:56,714
Can you save it?

7
00:01:56,738 --> 00:02:00,462
No. No way.
No, I gotta start over from scratch.

8
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:02,937
I'll call the studio
when the phones get back up,

9
00:02:02,962 --> 00:02:04,904
see if they can extend my deadline.

10
00:02:05,806 --> 00:02:07,467
What choice do they have?

11
00:02:10,609 --> 00:02:11,598
You kiddin'?

12
00:02:11,623 --> 00:02:14,161
They could whip up some bad
Photoshop poster in an afternoon.

13
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:16,403
They do it all the time. Two big heads.

14
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:18,817
I should have brought it downstairs
with me last night.

15
00:02:18,842 --> 00:02:20,034
Just stupid, I guess.

16
00:02:20,059 --> 00:02:21,475
Well, sweetie,

17
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,186
you couldn't exactly know that a tree
was gonna come flying through the window.

18
00:02:24,211 --> 00:02:27,164
Yeah, I'll hit the hardware store too,
get some plastic sheeting and duct tape

19
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:29,350
and seal this up
before it gets dark, you know.

20
00:02:29,375 --> 00:02:31,211
Order in some new glass.

21
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:36,598
Oh, you know what? That was your
grandfather's tree, the one he planted.

22
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:40,578
Used to play in that tree.
It's just stuff, though.

23
00:02:40,593 --> 00:02:43,118
You know, we're safe.
That's all that counts.

24
00:02:43,428 --> 00:02:44,405
Yeah.

25
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,021
Mom, Dad, you gotta come see!

26
00:02:46,046 --> 00:02:47,775
Hey, Billy, take it easy, all right?

27
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,770
I really don't want you running
all over the place.

28
00:02:49,795 --> 00:02:52,381
But you gotta come look.
The boathouse is all bashed!

29
00:02:52,412 --> 00:02:53,815
Holy crap!

30
00:02:54,006 --> 00:02:54,951
Billy.

31
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:58,053
Sorry, Mom, but you just gotta come!
Come on!

32
00:02:58,475 --> 00:02:59,404
Whoa!

33
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:01,434
Whoa.

34
00:03:01,459 --> 00:03:03,124
- Whoa.
- Come on.

35
00:03:03,428 --> 00:03:05,576
Having spoken, the Doomsayer departs.

36
00:03:05,601 --> 00:03:06,451
Come on!

37
00:03:08,015 --> 00:03:10,147
How do you two always manage
to make me laugh?

38
00:03:11,037 --> 00:03:13,668
- You have incredibly low standards.
- Mm-hmm.

39
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:16,860
Let's go, uh, see the damage.

40
00:03:16,885 --> 00:03:17,874
No.

41
00:03:22,669 --> 00:03:24,975
- Norton's tree.
- Yeah.

42
00:03:26,415 --> 00:03:29,476
You mean the dead one I've been
asking him to take down for three years

43
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:31,718
before it finally blew over?
That tree?

44
00:03:32,745 --> 00:03:34,702
Really got smooshed.

45
00:03:34,949 --> 00:03:36,257
You ain't kiddin'.

46
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,561
Look at that.

47
00:03:41,187 --> 00:03:42,569
What is it, Daddy?

48
00:03:43,752 --> 00:03:44,741
Mist.

49
00:03:45,902 --> 00:03:48,803
- On the lake?
- We've had mist on the lake before.

50
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:51,240
Coming off the mountain like that?

51
00:03:51,265 --> 00:03:53,265
Two fronts meeting,

52
00:03:53,447 --> 00:03:55,677
left over from the storm,
something like that.

53
00:03:56,311 --> 00:03:57,245
You sure?

54
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:58,905
Honey, I'm not the weatherman.

55
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:02,338
Why don't you take Billy, get him dressed.
I'll take him to town with me.

56
00:04:02,363 --> 00:04:03,851
Okay. Where you going?

57
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:07,021
I'm gonna go have a little chat
with our neighbor about his tree.

58
00:04:07,311 --> 00:04:08,242
Hon.

59
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:10,303
Don't worry, I'm not gonna
punch him in the nose.

60
00:04:10,328 --> 00:04:11,659
You know what he's gonna say.

61
00:04:11,684 --> 00:04:14,710
He's gonna say, "Sue me,"
which, I don't know, maybe we should.

62
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:19,132
Honey, one property dispute with
this guy is enough to last me a lifetime.

63
00:04:19,158 --> 00:04:21,568
I'm gonna ask for
his insurance information.

64
00:04:22,427 --> 00:04:23,405
Okay.

65
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:24,974
- That's all.
- Yeah.

66
00:04:28,132 --> 00:04:30,702
Ohh! Motherfucker!

67
00:04:33,673 --> 00:04:34,999
Aw, shit!

68
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:38,030
Ohh, you motherfucker!

69
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:40,046
Cock sucker!

70
00:04:42,181 --> 00:04:43,170
"Turn on.

71
00:04:43,671 --> 00:04:45,257
"Full choke.

72
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,991
Pull five... choke."

73
00:04:52,538 --> 00:04:54,028
I guess you've seen the...

74
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:56,474
...boathouse.

75
00:04:56,499 --> 00:04:57,749
Yeah, and...?

76
00:04:57,850 --> 00:04:59,046
Nothin'.

77
00:04:59,647 --> 00:05:02,744
Just think we should trade
insurance info, you know?

78
00:05:02,917 --> 00:05:04,046
That's all.

79
00:05:06,776 --> 00:05:09,267
Oh, my insurance guy's gonna love me.

80
00:05:11,856 --> 00:05:13,015
Oh.

81
00:05:13,491 --> 00:05:15,649
Shit. The 1980.

82
00:05:15,674 --> 00:05:17,390
I was gonna bring the station wagon, but...

83
00:05:18,697 --> 00:05:21,546
I don't know, the weather was so beautiful 
coming out of New York, I just...

84
00:05:21,711 --> 00:05:22,878
You know, top down.

85
00:05:22,903 --> 00:05:24,686
I'm sorry, man. I mean it.

86
00:05:25,149 --> 00:05:26,639
Sincerely.

87
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:29,138
That's nice of you to say.

88
00:05:29,168 --> 00:05:32,405
No, that car was cherry.
I hate to see it like that.

89
00:05:35,627 --> 00:05:36,837
Okay, I'll tell you what,

90
00:05:36,862 --> 00:05:39,578
I'll find my insurance guy's number,
I'll bring it by later.

91
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:41,466
- That okay?
- No problem.

92
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:48,812
So, uh, David,

93
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:54,066
you're not heading into town today
by any chance, are you?

94
00:06:08,634 --> 00:06:10,601
Well, CMP's out in force.

95
00:06:11,637 --> 00:06:13,054
Maybe we'll get our power back.

96
00:06:13,425 --> 00:06:14,949
I know. Some storm, huh?

97
00:06:14,974 --> 00:06:16,476
One for the books, yeah.

98
00:06:16,835 --> 00:06:20,560
For a moment there last night, I thought
we were gonna take off and head for Oz.

99
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:24,987
WZON is off the air,
but Portland's still broadcasting.

100
00:06:25,352 --> 00:06:26,341
Daddy, look.

101
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:27,962
Ah.

102
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,718
Guys from the base.

103
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,826
- From up the mountain?
- Uh-huh.

104
00:06:31,851 --> 00:06:33,437
The Arrowhead Project?

105
00:06:35,062 --> 00:06:37,893
Well, you're a local.
Any idea what they do up there?

106
00:06:38,047 --> 00:06:41,640
Missile defense research. You know, 
I'm sure you've heard the stories.

107
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:44,877
Oh, sure. The woman at
the Laundromat says that, uh,

108
00:06:45,054 --> 00:06:48,049
they have a crashed flying saucer
up there with frozen alien bodies.

109
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:49,837
Right. Miss Edna. Yeah.

110
00:06:50,054 --> 00:06:51,437
Miss Tabloid.

111
00:06:52,781 --> 00:06:55,359
"I Had Bigfoot's Baby."

112
00:06:56,664 --> 00:06:59,008
"Satan's Face Appears in Oil Well Fire."

113
00:06:59,033 --> 00:07:00,781
You know, real reliable stuff.

114
00:07:05,153 --> 00:07:06,643
Well, they're in a hurry.

115
00:07:07,035 --> 00:07:08,906
Maybe their power's out too.

116
00:07:17,835 --> 00:07:18,894
Huh. Still no signal.

117
00:07:19,534 --> 00:07:21,984
Why don't you go ahead?
I'm gonna try Steph on a pay phone.

118
00:07:22,009 --> 00:07:23,704
Can I go with Mr. Norton, Daddy?

119
00:07:24,144 --> 00:07:26,654
Sure, if you promise
to hold his hand, I guess.

120
00:07:26,679 --> 00:07:27,776
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

121
00:07:28,379 --> 00:07:29,390
Here's a list.

122
00:07:29,415 --> 00:07:30,840
- Sure.
- Okay?

123
00:07:31,019 --> 00:07:32,527
Meet you guys in there.

124
00:07:34,086 --> 00:07:35,075
Hold hands.

125
00:07:38,925 --> 00:07:41,189
I'm sorry.
I didn't know it was your sister.

126
00:07:45,716 --> 00:07:47,473
That looks so freaky!

127
00:07:47,643 --> 00:07:48,632
Hmm.

128
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,518
- Sally, hey.
- Hey, Mr. Drayton.

129
00:07:58,543 --> 00:08:00,088
You guys look jammed up.

130
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:03,124
Yeah, well, half the staff
didn't show, plus the power's out.

131
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,902
Oh, no. What, no backup generator?

132
00:08:05,965 --> 00:08:07,094
Only to keep the food cold.

133
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:09,846
Everything else, welcome to the
Dark Ages, and bring your checkbook.

134
00:08:09,871 --> 00:08:13,563
Hey, Thursday night, Steph and I 
want a date night. Baby-sit?

135
00:08:13,587 --> 00:08:15,277
Heck, yeah. I'm there.

136
00:08:16,513 --> 00:08:17,781
Oh, my God.

137
00:08:17,789 --> 00:08:22,586
The storm. Everybody's stockin' up. 
Been like this since we opened.

138
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:23,828
Crappy day, huh?

139
00:08:23,853 --> 00:08:26,344
Eh, everyone's a little pissed off 
this morning.

140
00:08:26,742 --> 00:08:28,573
'Morning, Mrs. Carmody.

141
00:08:29,192 --> 00:08:31,786
With lines like these,
I don't know how good it is,

142
00:08:31,811 --> 00:08:34,306
but I guess we'll have to make do.

143
00:08:34,981 --> 00:08:36,603
Keep your head down, pal.

144
00:08:36,628 --> 00:08:37,767
I know it.

145
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,309
Hey, champ.

146
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,234
Your wife should be a doctor.

147
00:08:45,236 --> 00:08:47,265
She could make a fortune in Manhattan
with this handwriting.

148
00:08:47,290 --> 00:08:49,971
Yeah, it takes some getting used to.

149
00:08:49,996 --> 00:08:52,315
Why don't you get your stuff?
I'll meet you at the checkout.

150
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,423
Okay, done.

151
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:59,130
Hey, David,
thanks for helping me out today.

152
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:05,395
Are you and Mr. Norton
gonna be friends now, Daddy?

153
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,944
Oh, I don't know.

154
00:09:08,228 --> 00:09:10,219
"Friends" might be stretching it a little.

155
00:09:11,121 --> 00:09:13,361
I guess you're not mad
at each other anymore.

156
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:14,375
I guess not.

157
00:09:16,239 --> 00:09:18,020
And that's a start, huh?

158
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:22,884
I'm sorry, ma'am, the registers are down.
The power outage got us too.

159
00:09:22,909 --> 00:09:25,442
Hopefully we'll have power up pretty soon.

160
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:38,203
- The bus leaves in 30 minutes.
- We'll make it, okay?

161
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,235
You guys get the goodies.
I'll wait in line.

162
00:09:45,651 --> 00:09:47,585
I need some change on register five.

163
00:09:49,221 --> 00:09:50,851
Good morning, Ms. Reppler.

164
00:09:51,324 --> 00:09:52,586
Hello, Ms. Reppler.

165
00:09:52,906 --> 00:09:57,556
Well, hello to you, Billy Drayton.
How'd you hold up in the storm?

166
00:09:57,581 --> 00:10:01,085
We had a tree come through the picture
window last night, right in my studio.

167
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:04,300
And the boathouse got all smooshed.
Mr. Norton's tree fell on it.

168
00:10:04,325 --> 00:10:05,280
Ouch.

169
00:10:05,305 --> 00:10:07,796
- Yeah.
- Sorry to hear that.

170
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:12,300
How'd you guys make out?

171
00:10:12,325 --> 00:10:15,387
Oh, we're fine.
It's the listings I'm worried about.

172
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:18,339
At the very least, I'll bet every one
of our "For Sale" signs fell over.

173
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:21,025
We had damage at the school,
wouldn't you know?

174
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:24,050
That's what we get for not fixing
that roof when we should've,

175
00:10:24,075 --> 00:10:27,141
but with funds being cut every year...

176
00:10:27,564 --> 00:10:31,534
You'd think educating children would
be more of a priority in this country,

177
00:10:31,559 --> 00:10:33,444
but you'd be wrong.

178
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:36,720
Government's got better things
to spend our money on,

179
00:10:36,736 --> 00:10:40,520
like corporate handouts
and building bombs.

180
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,834
Daddy, is there a fire? Is Mommy all right?

181
00:10:55,859 --> 00:10:58,419
I'm sure she's fine. Don't worry, okay?

182
00:10:59,734 --> 00:11:01,437
Mind what you're doing, Sally.

183
00:11:01,927 --> 00:11:04,687
Oh, come on, we got 10 days' leave.
Check our papers.

184
00:11:04,712 --> 00:11:07,875
Look, I told you, all leaves are cancelled.
I don't know why.

185
00:11:08,242 --> 00:11:09,944
I gotta go check the pharmacy out.

186
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:12,437
Three men meet me
back at the Jeep in five minutes.

187
00:11:12,714 --> 00:11:13,945
That's an order.

188
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:19,875
Shit, man! Another half an hour,
and we'd have been gone.

189
00:11:52,774 --> 00:11:54,366
Oh, my God!

190
00:12:02,306 --> 00:12:03,769
Something in the mist!

191
00:12:05,128 --> 00:12:07,580
Something in the mist took John Lee!

192
00:12:07,605 --> 00:12:09,158
Dan, catch your breath.

193
00:12:09,183 --> 00:12:10,871
Something in the mist took John Lee.

194
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:12,659
I could hear him screaming.

195
00:12:13,121 --> 00:12:15,710
Shut the doors! Shut the doors!
My God!

196
00:12:15,735 --> 00:12:17,480
Daddy, I'm scared. Can we go home?

197
00:12:21,961 --> 00:12:23,229
Don't go out there.

198
00:12:23,254 --> 00:12:25,604
There's something in the mist.
It took John Lee.

199
00:12:25,629 --> 00:12:27,822
Screw that! I'm gettin' in my car.

200
00:12:27,847 --> 00:12:29,129
Mister, no!

201
00:13:01,657 --> 00:13:03,910
Please hold me. Please.

202
00:13:03,944 --> 00:13:05,335
It's okay, it's okay.

203
00:13:05,428 --> 00:13:09,430
It's a pollution cloud.
The mills down in Rumford.

204
00:13:10,007 --> 00:13:12,549
Some kind of chemical explosion.
Has to be.

205
00:13:14,569 --> 00:13:15,780
What is it?

206
00:13:16,928 --> 00:13:18,624
What's going on?

207
00:13:21,522 --> 00:13:22,905
It's death.

208
00:13:57,991 --> 00:13:59,335
Stay down!

209
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:02,066
Daddy!

210
00:14:09,618 --> 00:14:10,846
You okay?

211
00:14:21,564 --> 00:14:23,150
That was an earthquake.

212
00:14:23,645 --> 00:14:26,281
I tell you, the goddamn mills blew up!

213
00:14:26,306 --> 00:14:29,643
Is everyone okay? Is anyone hurt?

214
00:14:29,668 --> 00:14:32,967
Everybody just stay put, okay?
Just stay inside the store.

215
00:14:33,275 --> 00:14:36,078
I can't. I can't stay here.
I gotta get home to my kids.

216
00:14:36,103 --> 00:14:39,119
No. No, don't go out there.

217
00:14:39,191 --> 00:14:41,989
It's death out there.
It's the end of days.

218
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:44,250
Stop it, okay? Stop it.

219
00:14:44,275 --> 00:14:47,476
Please, everybody,
everybody just relax, okay?

220
00:14:47,501 --> 00:14:50,487
He's right. Let's just stay cool.
Let's just try to figure out what happened.

221
00:14:50,512 --> 00:14:54,881
I'm sorry, I... I can't just stay here.
I have to get home to my kids.

222
00:14:54,906 --> 00:14:56,806
Ma'am, no, you can't go out there.

223
00:14:56,813 --> 00:14:58,706
Could be a poisonous gas cloud.

224
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,304
Didn't you hear that man screaming?

225
00:15:00,329 --> 00:15:02,970
I agree. Let's stay here
until we figure it out.

226
00:15:02,995 --> 00:15:04,564
You're not listening!

227
00:15:05,125 --> 00:15:07,056
I can't stay here.

228
00:15:07,905 --> 00:15:11,739
Wanda's looking after little Victor.
She's only 8.

229
00:15:11,764 --> 00:15:15,632
Sometimes she forgets
she's supposed to be watching him.

230
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:22,212
I told them I'd only be gone
a few minutes.

231
00:15:23,154 --> 00:15:25,142
She's only 8.

232
00:15:26,635 --> 00:15:27,781
For their sakes,

233
00:15:28,641 --> 00:15:29,781
don't.

234
00:15:34,499 --> 00:15:37,024
Well, isn't anybody gonna help me?

235
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:41,503
Shh. It's okay, pal.

236
00:15:42,708 --> 00:15:45,462
Won't somebody here see a lady home?

237
00:15:50,244 --> 00:15:51,290
You?

238
00:15:59,078 --> 00:16:00,102
You?

239
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:11,202
It's okay, buddy.

240
00:16:11,225 --> 00:16:11,845
You?

241
00:16:11,870 --> 00:16:15,532
Ma'am, please,
I got my own boy to worry about.

242
00:16:19,611 --> 00:16:21,855
I hope you all rot in hell.

243
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,681
Ma'am, please, wait until-

244
00:16:59,423 --> 00:17:01,744
Okay, let's start cleaning up, okay?

245
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:04,816
Get the spilled bottles, broken glass,
stuff like that.

246
00:17:04,829 --> 00:17:06,962
Aisle three has medical supplies.

247
00:17:08,204 --> 00:17:10,125
It's okay. It's okay.

248
00:17:10,195 --> 00:17:12,040
All right, easy, champ. Come on.

249
00:17:13,204 --> 00:17:17,603
Come on. All right, hey, hey, hey.
Can't keep crying like this, pal.

250
00:17:17,814 --> 00:17:18,879
Come on!

251
00:17:19,181 --> 00:17:20,948
Come on, you're gonna hurt yourself.

252
00:17:21,329 --> 00:17:23,350
- Come on, are you all right?
- I want Mommy!

253
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:25,212
