506
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:45,978
and you guys are backing him up.

507
00:34:46,003 --> 00:34:47,485
So winning wasn't enough, huh?

508
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:51,203
You wanted to humiliate me some more,
show me a rubber snake

509
00:34:51,228 --> 00:34:53,547
while these... these hicks stand
around laughing their asses off.

510
00:34:53,572 --> 00:34:54,834
- Watch who you callin' a hick!
- Myron! Myron!

511
00:34:54,859 --> 00:34:56,724
- Hey, hey, fuck...!
- Mr. Norton...

512
00:34:56,749 --> 00:34:59,343
...I swear, you have got us all wrong.

513
00:34:59,752 --> 00:35:04,014
You're not too crazy about,
um, out-of-towners, are you?

514
00:35:04,967 --> 00:35:06,959
I only spend my money,
and I pay my taxes here,

515
00:35:06,984 --> 00:35:10,852
and I have seen you
talking behind my back.

516
00:35:12,628 --> 00:35:14,263
Y'all stick together.

517
00:35:17,521 --> 00:35:18,891
Well, don't I feel foolish?

518
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:21,407
I actually thought you were
being kind to me today,

519
00:35:21,411 --> 00:35:23,105
and, well, thanks for setting me straight.

520
00:35:23,130 --> 00:35:26,224
And I'm glad that tree fell on
your boathouse, you know that? Glad.

521
00:35:26,249 --> 00:35:27,878
Smashed it in pretty good, didn't it?
Fantastic.

522
00:35:27,896 --> 00:35:29,402
Now, all of y'all, just stay out of my way.

523
00:35:29,427 --> 00:35:32,348
I know you're scared, man.
I'm scared too.

524
00:35:32,373 --> 00:35:34,173
- Lives are at stake around here.
- David...

525
00:35:34,198 --> 00:35:36,530
Okay, my son's life. Now, I need you.

526
00:35:36,551 --> 00:35:40,265
Brent, please,
get your head out of your ass.

527
00:35:40,307 --> 00:35:42,394
All right, I'll drag you back there 
if I have to.

528
00:35:42,419 --> 00:35:43,334
Come here.

529
00:35:43,359 --> 00:35:48,428
David, get your goddamn hands off of me!
I'll sue your ass again!

530
00:35:48,453 --> 00:35:50,834
Sue your ass,
and this time you'll go to jail!

531
00:35:51,107 --> 00:35:52,528
This man assaulted me.

532
00:35:52,561 --> 00:35:55,094
He assaulted me. You were witness to it.

533
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:56,114
This man's crazy. He's crazy-

534
00:35:56,133 --> 00:35:57,248
No.

535
00:35:57,889 --> 00:36:00,289
He isn't. I wish he was, but he isn't.

536
00:36:02,493 --> 00:36:06,623
E-Everyone in the store,
you want to come back here?

537
00:36:07,510 --> 00:36:10,717
There's something you need to hear.
It concerns you all.

538
00:36:11,037 --> 00:36:11,797
Okay.

539
00:36:11,822 --> 00:36:15,092
W-Wait. I don't know
what you people think you're doing.

540
00:36:15,490 --> 00:36:18,311
You're drinking? For Christ's sake, Ollie.

541
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:21,709
Do you want me to report you?
You want to lose your job?

542
00:36:22,123 --> 00:36:24,023
Look, I'm gonna be taking down names,
starting with you.

543
00:36:24,303 --> 00:36:26,058
And I am prepared to file a police report.

544
00:36:26,083 --> 00:36:28,426
- Fine, Bud, write down your names.
- I will.

545
00:36:28,451 --> 00:36:31,139
But in the meantime,
shut the fuck up and listen.

546
00:36:33,149 --> 00:36:34,695
This is Mr. David Drayton.

547
00:36:34,720 --> 00:36:37,567
You need to hear what he's got to say
if you're thinking about leaving.

548
00:36:37,592 --> 00:36:40,472
Go hang out with the ladies, all right?
Listen, don't be scared.

549
00:36:42,733 --> 00:36:43,722
It's okay.

550
00:36:45,976 --> 00:36:46,965
Okay.

551
00:36:48,105 --> 00:36:49,436
This is how it is.

552
00:36:49,725 --> 00:36:52,319
Now, I don't know what this mist is,

553
00:36:53,002 --> 00:36:55,424
but there are things in it, 
and they're dangerous, like Dan said.

554
00:36:55,448 --> 00:36:56,522
That's right.

555
00:36:57,139 --> 00:36:58,717
That's exactly right.

556
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:00,625
What kind of things?

557
00:37:00,650 --> 00:37:04,565
I never saw it. It happened too fast.
I got knocked down.

558
00:37:04,873 --> 00:37:06,959
Five of us went back in the loading dock.

559
00:37:07,436 --> 00:37:10,194
It was Jim, Myron, Ollie,

560
00:37:10,772 --> 00:37:13,791
me, Norm, the bag boy.

561
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:15,736
- We opened the door...
- Where's Norm?

562
00:37:15,761 --> 00:37:19,086
...so Norm could go out
and clear the vent for the generator.

563
00:37:20,529 --> 00:37:22,353
Something come out of the mist
and took him.

564
00:37:22,378 --> 00:37:23,367
Took him?

565
00:37:23,392 --> 00:37:24,803
What do you mean?

566
00:37:26,393 --> 00:37:27,553
Just... killed him.

567
00:37:27,578 --> 00:37:29,443
I mean dragged him off.

568
00:37:29,468 --> 00:37:34,030
Now, guys,
I don't know what these things are.

569
00:37:35,152 --> 00:37:37,014
All we saw were tentacles.

570
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:41,580
Tentacles?

571
00:37:44,996 --> 00:37:46,588
Tentacles, he says.

572
00:37:46,982 --> 00:37:49,075
Tentacles from Planet X.

573
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:53,732
It's a lie, you know. I mean, all these
people do is just lie each other up.

574
00:37:53,753 --> 00:37:54,981
It's a pile of shit.

575
00:37:55,006 --> 00:37:57,772
Of course it's a lie. Of course it's a lie.
It's lunacy.

576
00:37:58,576 --> 00:38:01,136
From the look of it, the tentacles
are coming out of the beer cans.

577
00:38:01,212 --> 00:38:04,170
All right, Bud, don't take our word for it.
Go look.

578
00:38:10,721 --> 00:38:11,710
Over there.

579
00:38:17,395 --> 00:38:19,053
What the hell is that?

580
00:38:51,362 --> 00:38:54,904
It appears we may have a problem
of some magnitude here.

581
00:39:10,881 --> 00:39:12,631
Yeah, just keep 'em in line. Thanks.

582
00:39:23,902 --> 00:39:25,563
Let me...

583
00:39:27,231 --> 00:39:30,598
...help these people.

584
00:39:31,053 --> 00:39:34,561
Let me... let me preach your word.

585
00:39:36,574 --> 00:39:41,670
Let me shine your light,
'cause they're not all bad.

586
00:39:42,579 --> 00:39:44,911
They can't all be bad.

587
00:39:47,961 --> 00:39:51,842
Some can be saved, can't they?

588
00:39:52,209 --> 00:39:53,412
Yes.

589
00:39:53,758 --> 00:39:59,525
Some can be brought...
to heaven's holy gates through your grace.

590
00:39:59,645 --> 00:40:05,623
I have to believe that, though I know
most will swim in the lake of fire forever.

591
00:40:08,939 --> 00:40:10,951
If I can save a few...

592
00:40:12,051 --> 00:40:14,042
...even one...

593
00:40:14,945 --> 00:40:17,733
...then my life will have counted
for something.

594
00:40:18,494 --> 00:40:24,719
I will have pulled my weight. I will
have earned my place at your side.

595
00:40:24,744 --> 00:40:29,293
I will have served a purpose
here on this earth.

596
00:40:29,318 --> 00:40:30,412
Hello?

597
00:40:46,858 --> 00:40:48,120
What?

598
00:40:48,496 --> 00:40:50,375
I just need to use the bathroom.

599
00:40:50,822 --> 00:40:51,811
Oh.

600
00:40:52,798 --> 00:40:55,198
Okay. Well, then, have at it.

601
00:40:59,145 --> 00:41:00,373
Ma'am...

602
00:41:01,660 --> 00:41:04,933
I... I just want you to know
that it's okay...

603
00:41:05,404 --> 00:41:08,105
...being scared, I mean and...

604
00:41:08,551 --> 00:41:12,445
well, if you need a friend,
you know, someone to talk to.

605
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:18,484
I have a friend...
God up above. I talk to him every day.

606
00:41:18,509 --> 00:41:20,500
Don't you condescend to me.

607
00:41:20,722 --> 00:41:21,754
I'm sorry?

608
00:41:21,779 --> 00:41:25,097
Not ever. You don't mock me.

609
00:41:25,122 --> 00:41:27,090
That's not what I was doing.

610
00:41:28,027 --> 00:41:32,488
Well, I'll tell you what...
the day I need a friend like you,

611
00:41:32,513 --> 00:41:35,443
I'll just have myself a little squat
and shit one out.

612
00:41:40,898 --> 00:41:42,761
Maybe you do believe this.

613
00:41:42,786 --> 00:41:46,019
Maybe they're not lies,
they're delusions. Whatever.

614
00:41:46,044 --> 00:41:50,017
Uh, the fact remains, the evidence here
is flimsy. It's bordering on ludicrous.

615
00:41:50,041 --> 00:41:51,669
Hey, this isn't a courtroom.

616
00:41:52,196 --> 00:41:53,185
You're not arguing a case,

617
00:41:53,210 --> 00:41:54,910
and you're doing nothing but damage,
talking the way you are.

618
00:41:54,935 --> 00:41:57,890
And you can throw as much cow's blood
around the loading dock as you want to.

619
00:41:57,915 --> 00:41:59,442
You still haven't fooled anyone.

620
00:41:59,467 --> 00:42:00,525
Leave it alone, David.

621
00:42:00,550 --> 00:42:04,310
You can't convince some people there's
a fire even when their hair is burning.

622
00:42:04,335 --> 00:42:05,931
Denial is a powerful thing.

623
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:10,808
Well, keep talking. I'll have no part
of it, nor would any thinking person.

624
00:42:10,833 --> 00:42:13,172
Keep thinking, Mr. Lawyer.

625
00:42:13,474 --> 00:42:16,175
There's no defense against the will of God.

626
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:18,395
There's no court of appeals in hell.

627
00:42:19,013 --> 00:42:20,960
There's no defense here, either.

628
00:42:20,985 --> 00:42:23,215
Not even with all the fertilizer
in the world,

629
00:42:23,240 --> 00:42:25,731
not even if you stack it
as high as you can.

630
00:42:25,756 --> 00:42:28,387
It's still just bags of shit, isn't it?

631
00:42:28,421 --> 00:42:30,508
Those of you who want to discuss
this thing rationally

632
00:42:30,533 --> 00:42:34,326
to find a means of rescue
are welcome to join me.

633
00:42:34,585 --> 00:42:37,247
Those who want to stack dog food,

634
00:42:37,676 --> 00:42:39,245
knock yourselves out.

635
00:42:42,818 --> 00:42:46,189
We got those windows taped up
as best we could. It should help.

636
00:42:46,214 --> 00:42:47,763
Yeah, think so?

637
00:42:49,632 --> 00:42:51,802
Duct tape and dog food bags.

638
00:42:53,716 --> 00:42:55,047
That bad?

639
00:42:55,141 --> 00:42:56,130
It's not good.

640
00:42:56,155 --> 00:42:59,318
There's none so blind
as those who will not see.

641
00:43:00,629 --> 00:43:04,510
Open your eyes.
Let the scales fall away.

642
00:43:04,683 --> 00:43:06,674
This has all been written.

643
00:43:08,130 --> 00:43:11,463
Revelations, chapter 15:

644
00:43:11,759 --> 00:43:16,071
"And the temple was filled with smoke
from the glory of God

645
00:43:16,096 --> 00:43:19,494
"and from his power,
and no one could enter the temple

646
00:43:19,505 --> 00:43:23,583
until the seven plagues of the seven angels
were completed."

647
00:43:23,779 --> 00:43:25,579
Well, what are you saying?

648
00:43:25,648 --> 00:43:27,088
What are you proposing?

649
00:43:27,113 --> 00:43:29,052
That we all prepare...

650
00:43:30,191 --> 00:43:31,862
...to meet our Maker.

651
00:43:31,878 --> 00:43:34,039
Oh, prepare to meet shit!

652
00:43:34,831 --> 00:43:39,281
Lady, your tongue must be hung in the
middle so that it can waggle at both ends.

653
00:43:39,306 --> 00:43:43,097
The end time has come,
not in flames, but in mist.

654
00:43:43,122 --> 00:43:44,063
Come here!

655
00:43:44,088 --> 00:43:45,214
Easy! Back off!

656
00:43:45,239 --> 00:43:49,435
How about if your ass prepares to meet
my size-10 work boot. How about that?

657
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:51,271
Hey, there's no call for that.

658
00:43:51,458 --> 00:43:53,639
Myron, please, calm your friend down.

659
00:43:53,664 --> 00:43:56,524
I'm trying to save your soul,
you stupid man.

660
00:43:56,549 --> 00:43:58,744
- Doubters will doubt till the end.
- It's okay.

661
00:43:58,769 --> 00:43:59,878
No, I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

662
00:43:59,903 --> 00:44:02,497
A monstrosity did pull that poor boy away.

663
00:44:03,118 --> 00:44:06,485
Things in the mist... do you doubt?

664
00:44:06,510 --> 00:44:07,720
Do you?

665
00:44:09,122 --> 00:44:10,767
Then go out.

666
00:44:11,243 --> 00:44:13,492
Go out and say, "How do you do."

667
00:44:13,517 --> 00:44:14,837
Shut up, lady.

668
00:44:16,487 --> 00:44:17,640
For God's sakes.

669
00:44:17,665 --> 00:44:19,732
Look, you'll have to stop now.
You're scaring the children.

670
00:44:19,757 --> 00:44:21,156
They should be scared.

671
00:44:21,759 --> 00:44:24,259
Oh, yes, they should.

672
00:44:24,996 --> 00:44:30,128
Their beautiful, pure little minds
have been corrupted with lies.

673
00:44:30,154 --> 00:44:31,143
Lies.

674
00:44:31,168 --> 00:44:35,861
All this talk of a modern God,
or no God.

675
00:44:36,155 --> 00:44:37,816
There is one God.

676
00:44:38,064 --> 00:44:39,751
The God of the Israelites.

677
00:44:40,013 --> 00:44:45,091
And he is a stern and vengeful God,
and we have been mocking him far too long,

678
00:44:45,115 --> 00:44:48,778
and now he demands retribution in blood.

679
00:44:48,895 --> 00:44:52,109
It is time to declare yourselves.

680
00:44:52,148 --> 00:44:55,254
Take sides...
the saved and the damned.

681
00:44:55,279 --> 00:44:58,771
Read the Good Book. It calls for expiation.

682
00:44:58,796 --> 00:45:00,627
- Blood!
- What?

683
00:45:00,698 --> 00:45:01,915
Blood.

684
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,741
Little Normie was first,
and now God calls the rest of us.

685
00:45:08,039 --> 00:45:10,935
The bill is due. It must be paid.

686
00:45:10,960 --> 00:45:15,467
As Abraham prepared to sacrifice 
his only son to prove his love for God, so-

687
00:45:15,492 --> 00:45:16,978
Enough.

688
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:26,932
Another down payment.
A few more pennies in the jar.

689
00:45:27,142 --> 00:45:30,164
Now, that's nice, see.
I can't smack her, but it's okay for you.

690
00:45:30,189 --> 00:45:31,437
I-I'm sorry everybody,

691
00:45:31,462 --> 00:45:34,454
but this lady's perspective is
a little too Old Testament for my taste.

692
00:45:34,711 --> 00:45:36,353
They'll come for you.

693
00:45:37,196 --> 00:45:39,687
Maybe tonight, when darkness comes.

694
00:45:41,148 --> 00:45:44,618
They'll come tonight,
and they'll take someone else.

695
00:45:44,822 --> 00:45:46,118
See if they don't.

696
00:45:46,702 --> 00:45:50,792
And when they do, you will cry to God,

697
00:45:50,812 --> 00:45:54,546
and you will beg Mother Carmody
to show you the way.

698
00:45:54,571 --> 00:45:55,902
That's fine.

699
00:45:56,892 --> 00:46:01,523
But until then, if you don't shut up,
I'll wrap this tape around your mouth.

700
00:46:01,548 --> 00:46:03,671
You just try it, Ollie Weeks.

701
00:46:03,696 --> 00:46:05,186
And you, bitch...

702
00:46:06,563 --> 00:46:10,361
...you hit me again if you dare.

703
00:46:11,235 --> 00:46:14,478
You'll be on your knees to me
before this is through.

704
00:46:20,864 --> 00:46:23,453
Those of you who aren't local
should know that Mrs. Carmody

705
00:46:23,462 --> 00:46:27,459
is known in town for being... unstable.

706
00:46:27,484 --> 00:46:31,173
No shit. What was your first clue?

707
00:46:34,144 --> 00:46:35,204
Shh.

708
00:46:36,438 --> 00:46:37,712
Hi.

709
00:46:38,129 --> 00:46:39,651
What's up, little dude?

710
00:46:39,676 --> 00:46:41,637
How come your friends don't come get us?

711
00:46:41,662 --> 00:46:45,885
They got tanks and stuff, right?
Why can't you just call 'em?

712
00:46:46,251 --> 00:46:47,516
Phones don't work.

713
00:46:47,540 --> 00:46:49,072
But don't you got, like, a radio?

714
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,703
Hey, champ, what's going on?

715
00:46:50,725 --> 00:46:52,771
I want their friends to come rescue us.

716
00:46:52,796 --> 00:46:54,945
They would if they could, pal.
They're stuck here just like us.

717
00:46:54,970 --> 00:46:56,025
- But...
- Shh.

718
00:46:56,066 --> 00:46:57,904
Now, guys, we could use a hand over there.

719
00:46:57,923 --> 00:46:58,901
Yeah, sure thing.

720
00:46:58,926 --> 00:47:00,359
Troop, off your asses.

721
00:47:00,837 --> 00:47:03,495
- You all right?
- I don't like that scary lady.

722
00:47:03,814 --> 00:47:05,852
Oh, man, I don't either.

723
00:47:06,477 --> 00:47:07,944
But you know what?

724
00:47:08,337 --> 00:47:10,501
Maybe she's scared too.

725
00:47:11,195 --> 00:47:12,423
You think?

726
00:47:13,370 --> 00:47:15,126
You think Mommy's okay?

727
00:47:17,197 --> 00:47:18,376
Billy...

728
00:47:21,133 --> 00:47:23,139
I'm sorry about the times I was bad to her.

729
00:47:23,164 --> 00:47:24,283
Aw, hey.

730
00:47:25,293 --> 00:47:30,079
Mommy loves you very much.
And I'll bet she's fine.

731
00:47:31,970 --> 00:47:33,792
And I promise you,

732
00:47:33,817 --> 00:47:37,095
I'm gonna do everything I can
to get us back to her.

733
00:47:38,650 --> 00:47:40,015
- Okay?
- 'Kay.

734
00:47:40,883 --> 00:47:42,316
- Yeah?
- 'Kay.

735
00:47:43,751 --> 00:47:47,694
So, we can use the charcoal fluid 
and the mops to make torches.

736
00:47:47,698 --> 00:47:49,828
And we've got knives and stuff, God knows.

737
00:47:49,864 --> 00:47:55,079
This may be a silly question, Bud, but...
do you happen to have a gun in the store?

738
00:47:56,134 --> 00:47:59,570
Here? No. Please. 
This... this isn't Los Angeles.

739
00:47:59,595 --> 00:48:01,595
I've got a shotgun in my truck.

740
00:48:02,647 --> 00:48:04,236
I could try for it if you want.

741
00:48:04,261 --> 00:48:06,525
Oh, God, I don't think 
that'd be a good idea, Mr. Cornell.

742
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:07,743
Hold on.

743
00:48:10,053 --> 00:48:11,520
This gun, um...

744
00:48:11,947 --> 00:48:13,532
...my husband's idea.

745
00:48:13,557 --> 00:48:15,650
He's away on business a lot.

746
00:48:15,675 --> 00:48:16,835
It's not even loaded.

747
00:48:16,860 --> 00:48:18,487
Ain't much use unloaded, ma'am.

748
00:48:18,512 --> 00:48:19,501
Um...

749
00:48:23,092 --> 00:48:24,710
You know how to use that?

750
00:48:24,735 --> 00:48:28,079
Well, I shot it once on a pistol range.
Hit the target a few times.

751
00:48:28,772 --> 00:48:31,366
So, we got a gun.

752
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:35,165
