it's gonna drain 'em quick.

831
00:54:44,589 --> 00:54:45,547
How quick?

832
00:54:45,574 --> 00:54:47,774
- Five minutes, maybe ten.
- Yeah, if that.

833
00:54:47,799 --> 00:54:49,948
Okay, emergencies only.

834
00:54:50,677 --> 00:54:52,550
If something gets in the store.

835
00:55:01,048 --> 00:55:02,585
Holy Jesus, you scared the shit outta me.

836
00:55:02,610 --> 00:55:04,261
Oh, Sally, I'm sorry, really.

837
00:55:05,670 --> 00:55:08,503
I thought I'd come in and say hi
and see how you were holding up.

838
00:55:09,082 --> 00:55:10,572
- Hi.
- Hi.

839
00:55:11,176 --> 00:55:12,691
Barely. How about you?

840
00:55:12,809 --> 00:55:16,863
I'm worried about my folks, I guess.
You know, they live up on Shorm Road.

841
00:55:16,888 --> 00:55:18,913
That's less than five miles from here.

842
00:55:19,262 --> 00:55:20,866
How 'bout yours?

843
00:55:20,891 --> 00:55:25,840
Well, they're out of town right now.
They're at my aunt's in Boston, so...

844
00:55:25,865 --> 00:55:28,629
That's lucky. That means they're okay.

845
00:55:29,088 --> 00:55:30,418
I hope so.

846
00:55:32,474 --> 00:55:35,913
So... how soon you shipping out?

847
00:55:36,255 --> 00:55:38,152
Uh, couple weeks.

848
00:55:39,388 --> 00:55:41,254
Scared about going over there?

849
00:55:42,229 --> 00:55:43,199
Yeah.

850
00:55:48,657 --> 00:55:50,215
- Hey, Wayne?
- Hmm?

851
00:55:51,171 --> 00:55:53,074
How come you never asked me out?

852
00:55:53,966 --> 00:55:56,738
We flirted all through high school.
I know you like me.

853
00:56:00,767 --> 00:56:02,199
So how come?

854
00:56:04,677 --> 00:56:06,621
I'm stupid, I guess.

855
00:56:23,130 --> 00:56:25,181
Oh, shit! I'm sorry.

856
00:56:25,206 --> 00:56:26,548
Don't be. I just...

857
00:56:27,134 --> 00:56:29,806
I just didn't really want it
to happen like this, you know?

858
00:56:29,831 --> 00:56:32,026
Some shitty locker room at work.

859
00:56:33,054 --> 00:56:35,072
Can we just stay in here a while, then?

860
00:56:35,987 --> 00:56:37,876
I mean, just... just you and me.

861
00:56:49,788 --> 00:56:52,073
The parking lot lamps turned on.

862
00:56:52,452 --> 00:56:53,435
They're on a timer.

863
00:56:53,460 --> 00:56:55,444
Must be a different one that's live.

864
00:56:55,741 --> 00:57:00,210
Maybe we could tie into them somehow,
get some electricity in here.

865
00:57:01,153 --> 00:57:03,187
That'd mean walking out the door.

866
00:57:14,890 --> 00:57:15,760
God!

867
00:57:16,222 --> 00:57:17,689
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

868
00:57:17,882 --> 00:57:19,679
David! David!

869
00:57:23,407 --> 00:57:24,499
Look!

870
00:57:47,895 --> 00:57:49,106
My God.

871
00:58:04,538 --> 00:58:06,291
Are those bugs?

872
00:58:07,941 --> 00:58:09,580
Not like any I've ever seen.

873
00:58:10,445 --> 00:58:14,688
"They came out of the smoke,
locusts upon the earth,

874
00:58:14,713 --> 00:58:21,214
"and unto them was given power even
as the scorpions of the earth have power."

875
00:58:21,752 --> 00:58:22,791
Wow.

876
00:58:24,385 --> 00:58:26,471
Look at those stingers.

877
00:58:29,796 --> 00:58:31,619
Dear God.

878
00:59:10,868 --> 00:59:12,358
Holy shit!

879
00:59:28,510 --> 00:59:30,057
Myron, get the ones in the back!

880
00:59:31,405 --> 00:59:33,236
God, I think they're attracted
to the light.

881
00:59:33,916 --> 00:59:35,491
Look out, look out, look out!

882
00:59:35,562 --> 00:59:37,096
The light! Douse the light!

883
00:59:38,331 --> 00:59:39,662
Look out! Look out!

884
00:59:44,668 --> 00:59:45,930
Move! Move!

885
00:59:47,822 --> 00:59:49,885
Light, light, light, light, light!

886
00:59:51,546 --> 00:59:55,219
"And there came a voice from the temple 
saying to the seven angels,

887
00:59:55,244 --> 01:00:01,748
"'Go your ways and pour out the vials
of the wrath of God upon the earth."'

888
01:00:10,663 --> 01:00:13,244
Ollie, the glass is gonna give!

889
01:00:20,907 --> 01:00:21,799
Shit!

890
01:00:21,827 --> 01:00:23,707
Oh, my God, they turned on all the lights!

891
01:00:23,713 --> 01:00:25,518
- Jim! Myron!
- Fire!

892
01:00:25,543 --> 01:00:27,109
- Fire! Lighter!
- Douse the lights!

893
01:00:27,299 --> 01:00:28,752
Come on, come on!

894
01:00:32,685 --> 01:00:33,674
Whoa!

895
01:00:41,471 --> 01:00:42,854
Sally, look out!

896
01:00:44,691 --> 01:00:45,680
No!

897
01:00:54,195 --> 01:00:56,284
Let me see, let me see.
Let me see, sweetheart, let me see.

898
01:00:56,309 --> 01:00:58,340
No, you're gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay.

899
01:00:58,363 --> 01:00:59,660
Let me see. Let me see.

900
01:00:59,664 --> 01:01:01,122
You're fine. You're gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay.

901
01:01:01,157 --> 01:01:02,913
Give me the lighter! Put it on fire!

902
01:01:02,939 --> 01:01:03,928
Come on!

903
01:01:10,590 --> 01:01:12,882
Goddamn childproofing sons of bitches!

904
01:01:14,794 --> 01:01:17,058
Oh, shoot it! Shoot it!

905
01:01:18,945 --> 01:01:20,408
Shoot it! Shoot it!

906
01:01:20,433 --> 01:01:22,060
I can't! I'll smash the window!

907
01:01:23,138 --> 01:01:24,142
God!

908
01:01:24,150 --> 01:01:25,945
Oh, God! Ohh!

909
01:01:28,647 --> 01:01:29,851
Go! Go!

910
01:01:31,892 --> 01:01:33,351
Get down!

911
01:01:40,030 --> 01:01:41,255
Shit!

912
01:01:51,074 --> 01:01:53,091
- Ollie, you want these lights on or off?
- Leave 'em on.

913
01:01:59,272 --> 01:02:00,364
Oh, God!

914
01:02:02,184 --> 01:02:03,270
Kill it!

915
01:02:11,895 --> 01:02:14,318
Bring torches!
Bring something to keep 'em out!

916
01:02:14,323 --> 01:02:15,252
Come on.

917
01:02:17,182 --> 01:02:18,342
Sally!

918
01:02:30,071 --> 01:02:32,301
Where are the goddamn extinguishers?

919
01:02:42,849 --> 01:02:44,180
Get it! Get it! Get it!

920
01:02:49,823 --> 01:02:52,567
Bring torches.
We need torches at the window!

921
01:02:52,787 --> 01:02:54,143
Plug that hole!

922
01:03:01,734 --> 01:03:02,455
Dad!

923
01:03:08,782 --> 01:03:10,477
Down! Down! Lay down!

924
01:03:27,121 --> 01:03:28,110
My life...

925
01:03:29,080 --> 01:03:32,538
My life for you, your will be done.

926
01:03:46,526 --> 01:03:47,620
Daddy!

927
01:03:48,260 --> 01:03:49,651
Daddy!

928
01:04:05,594 --> 01:04:07,709
- No! Billy!
- Daddy!

929
01:04:07,906 --> 01:04:09,570
- Billy!
- Daddy!

930
01:04:23,094 --> 01:04:24,000
Billy!

931
01:04:24,695 --> 01:04:26,445
- Dad!
- Billy, come back here.

932
01:04:28,559 --> 01:04:30,461
- Dad!
- Billy, please!

933
01:04:36,872 --> 01:04:38,008
Billy!

934
01:05:07,157 --> 01:05:10,419
- Come on, let's move it!
- Somebody please come over here and help.

935
01:05:10,733 --> 01:05:12,394
Here's some tape!

936
01:05:14,108 --> 01:05:16,269
I'm right here.
I'm right here. Don't worry.

937
01:05:17,251 --> 01:05:19,185
Hurry up with the blankets!

938
01:05:19,472 --> 01:05:22,216
It hurts so bad! Please!

939
01:05:30,026 --> 01:05:31,687
It hurts so bad!

940
01:05:32,051 --> 01:05:33,443
Block it up here.

941
01:05:34,120 --> 01:05:35,883
Get me some more bags!

942
01:05:36,989 --> 01:05:39,763
Did we get 'em? Did we get 'em all?

943
01:05:40,526 --> 01:05:42,060
She was right.

944
01:05:42,576 --> 01:05:47,208
She said that it would happen like this.
She said that they would come at night.

945
01:05:47,945 --> 01:05:50,169
She told us someone would die.

946
01:06:14,883 --> 01:06:16,357
Mommy.

947
01:06:17,519 --> 01:06:22,201
Oh, shh, shh, shh. It's okay.
It's okay, it was just a dream.

948
01:06:23,114 --> 01:06:24,669
It's just a bad dream.

949
01:06:25,304 --> 01:06:27,067
I want my mommy.

950
01:06:27,446 --> 01:06:31,130
I know. I know. Of course you do.

951
01:06:31,143 --> 01:06:33,703
- Shh.
- I wanna go home.

952
01:06:33,982 --> 01:06:35,472
Just sleep.

953
01:06:36,734 --> 01:06:38,849
Everything'll be better in the morning.

954
01:06:45,233 --> 01:06:46,865
Think he likes you.

955
01:06:49,051 --> 01:06:51,154
Well, I hate that I had to lie to him.

956
01:06:52,926 --> 01:06:54,431
You have kids?

957
01:06:54,458 --> 01:06:55,476
No.

958
01:06:55,993 --> 01:07:00,802
I always wanted to, but...
things haven't been working out.

959
01:07:03,040 --> 01:07:05,841
Right now I'm thinking
maybe that's for the best.

960
01:07:07,388 --> 01:07:12,444
I saw creatures fly into the store tonight 
that... they shouldn't exist.

961
01:07:13,953 --> 01:07:16,444
I keep thinking 
I'm gonna wake up in a rubber room.

962
01:07:18,253 --> 01:07:19,810
You're not alone in that.

963
01:07:20,192 --> 01:07:22,122
We're all right there with you.

964
01:07:22,997 --> 01:07:24,927
This isn't gonna end, is it?

965
01:07:27,763 --> 01:07:28,752
David.

966
01:07:29,880 --> 01:07:32,110
It's Joe. He's getting worse.

967
01:07:51,122 --> 01:07:52,326
Joe.

968
01:07:53,799 --> 01:07:55,841
How you holdin' up, partner?

969
01:07:56,454 --> 01:07:59,747
David... is that you?

970
01:08:00,213 --> 01:08:01,966
Yeah, pal, how you doin'?

971
01:08:02,927 --> 01:08:05,246
It's bad. He's bad.

972
01:08:05,614 --> 01:08:08,242
Didn't know anything could hurt like this.

973
01:08:08,681 --> 01:08:11,232
If you guys can't help me...

974
01:08:12,757 --> 01:08:15,055
...y-you gotta end it, okay?

975
01:08:17,283 --> 01:08:19,683
Ollie's got that gun, right?

976
01:08:21,294 --> 01:08:23,364
- Right?
- No. No way.

977
01:08:23,389 --> 01:08:28,002
You can't fuck with me on this, bro.
Not with me like this.

978
01:08:28,442 --> 01:08:32,397
I'll do it. Just give me the gun.

979
01:08:32,431 --> 01:08:33,833
Hey, hey. Shh.

980
01:08:34,023 --> 01:08:37,117
- We're not there yet, okay?
- Oh, please!

981
01:08:37,521 --> 01:08:38,958
Joe, now, listen.

982
01:08:40,116 --> 01:08:43,399
Pal... we're gonna work something out.

983
01:08:43,424 --> 01:08:46,202
I just need you to hang in a little longer,
okay? Can we do that?

984
01:08:50,355 --> 01:08:52,372
Stay with him. I'll be back.

985
01:08:55,120 --> 01:08:59,380
Hattie, I need to go to the bathroom.
Will you watch Billy?

986
01:09:01,327 --> 01:09:02,544
Hattie.

987
01:09:19,234 --> 01:09:20,607
See anything?

988
01:09:21,241 --> 01:09:24,154
The last of those bugs
went away about four.

989
01:09:24,282 --> 01:09:25,677
Dawn's coming.

990
01:09:26,502 --> 01:09:27,833
What's on your mind?

991
01:09:27,858 --> 01:09:29,013
It's Joe.

992
01:09:30,712 --> 01:09:33,631
We don't get him on some serious
antibiotics, he's gonna die of infection.

993
01:09:33,628 --> 01:09:36,176
Plus he needs painkillers in the worst way.

994
01:09:36,185 --> 01:09:39,774
All... all... all we got here
is liquor and aspirin.

995
01:09:40,093 --> 01:09:42,724
You... You thinkin' about goin'
to that pharmacy next door?

996
01:09:42,720 --> 01:09:46,584
Irene Reppler says they've got Silvadene...
you know, the stuff they use in burn wards.

997
01:09:46,599 --> 01:09:47,771
She knows where they keep it.

998
01:09:47,809 --> 01:09:50,649
Slow down. You can't actually 
be thinkin' of doin' this.

999
01:09:50,675 --> 01:09:52,575
I'm also thinkin' beyond that.

1000
01:09:53,064 --> 01:09:56,580
We have to get out of here.
I mean permanently.

1001
01:09:56,605 --> 01:09:58,971
Why? We got plenty to eat!

1002
01:09:58,996 --> 01:10:01,829
What happens when one of those things
decides to break through this window?

1003
01:10:01,864 --> 01:10:04,830
I'm talkin' one of the big ones,
like the one that killed Norm.

1004
01:10:04,850 --> 01:10:07,568
Yeah, and that flaming torch idea
didn't work so well, did it?

1005
01:10:07,593 --> 01:10:10,061
We almost burned the goddamn store down.

1006
01:10:16,095 --> 01:10:17,426
It's Hattie.

1007
01:10:24,169 --> 01:10:25,329
Here?

1008
01:10:25,413 --> 01:10:27,672
All right, gently, now. Gently.

1009
01:10:27,697 --> 01:10:29,811
One... two... three.

1010
01:10:39,318 --> 01:10:43,493
I don't know how long she was there
like that, lying there next to us.

1011
01:10:43,512 --> 01:10:45,173
I thought she was sleeping.

1012
01:10:46,145 --> 01:10:49,459
I got my 4-wheel drive. It's out there.

1013
01:10:49,722 --> 01:10:51,629
Y-You're talking about leaving?

1014
01:10:52,538 --> 01:10:56,060
Well, we... should hit the pharmacy first.

1015
01:10:56,085 --> 01:10:58,337
We gotta bring back supplies 
for the injured.

1016
01:10:58,362 --> 01:11:01,418
I mean, if we don't, Joe Eagleton's
gonna die, and we can't let that happen.

1017
01:11:02,165 --> 01:11:03,325
But after that...

1018
01:11:04,270 --> 01:11:05,893
Look, my Land Cruiser
can hold eight people.

1019
01:11:05,918 --> 01:11:07,948
I say we drive south
as far as the fuel takes us

1020
01:11:07,973 --> 01:11:09,777
and try to get clear of this mist.

1021
01:11:10,606 --> 01:11:11,934
That's it?

1022
01:11:12,436 --> 01:11:13,767
That's the plan?

1023
01:11:13,769 --> 01:11:14,930
That's what I got.

1024
01:11:14,954 --> 01:11:17,805
No, you can't mean it. Not after 
what happened to Norton and his group.

1025
01:11:17,830 --> 01:11:20,298
No, no, no. Amanda, think.

1026
01:11:20,401 --> 01:11:24,034
Norton got over 200 feet from this store.
That's how much rope played out.

1027
01:11:24,055 --> 01:11:26,580
I'm parked half that distance
from here.

1028
01:11:26,605 --> 01:11:30,217
But who knows how far this mist has spread?
It could be the entire eastern seaboard.

1029
01:11:30,242 --> 01:11:32,815
Yeah, it could be the whole world,
for all we know.

1030
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:35,823
Wouldn't make us any less dead,
now, would it?

1031
01:11:35,941 --> 01:11:37,725
We have one gun.

1032
01:11:38,004 --> 01:11:39,793
- How many rounds?
- We got ten left.

1033
01:11:39,818 --> 01:11:41,098
Ten rounds. Jesus.

1034
01:11:41,123 --> 01:11:42,957
Okay, so ten.

1035
01:11:43,742 --> 01:11:47,504
Want another reason to get the hell
out of here? I'll give you the best one.

1036
01:11:48,093 --> 01:11:49,082
Her.

1037
01:11:50,018 --> 01:11:54,334
Mrs. Carmody. She's our very own Jim Jones.

1038
01:11:54,562 --> 01:11:57,078
I'd like to leave before 
people start drinking the Kool-Aid.

1039
01:11:57,103 --> 01:12:00,548
He's right. Flakier people get, 
the better she's gonna look.

1040
01:12:00,566 --> 01:12:03,407
No, I don't buy that. 
It's obvious she's nuts.

1041
01:12:03,426 --> 01:12:04,852
Look, a few people maybe, but-

1042
01:12:04,877 --> 01:12:07,175
No, I count four.
She's preachin' to 'em right now.

1043
01:12:07,200 --> 01:12:08,839
By noon, she'll have four more.

1044
01:12:08,878 --> 01:12:12,720
By tomorrow night, when those things
come back, she'll have a congregation,

1045
01:12:12,745 --> 01:12:16,331
and then we can start worryin'
about who she's gonna sacrifice

1046
01:12:16,356 --> 01:12:18,079
to make it all better.

1047
01:12:18,104 --> 01:12:19,275
Hmm?

1048
01:12:19,782 --> 01:12:22,922
You, Amanda? My little boy?

1049
01:12:23,275 --> 01:12:24,638
He's right.

1050
01:12:24,881 --> 01:12:27,423
You don't have much faith in humanity,
do you?

1051
01:12:28,219 --> 01:12:29,349
None whatsoever.

1052
01:12:29,354 --> 01:12:30,972
I can't accept that.

1053
01:12:31,013 --> 01:12:33,661
People are basically good, decent.

1054
01:12:33,686 --> 01:12:35,998
My God, David, we're a civilized society.

1055
01:12:36,023 --> 01:12:38,817
Sure, as long as the machines
are workin' and you can dial 9-1-1,

1056
01:12:38,854 --> 01:12:42,229
but you take those things away,
you throw people in the dark,

1057
01:12:42,233 --> 01:12:45,991
you scare the shit out of them,
no more rules,

1058
01:12:46,016 --> 01:12:47,843
you'll see how primitive they get.

1059
01:12:47,868 --> 01:12:52,875
You scare people badly enough,
you can get 'em to do anything.

1060
01:12:53,310 --> 01:12:58,158
They'll turn to whoever
promises a solution, or whatever.

1061
01:12:58,183 --> 01:13:00,343
Ollie, please, back me up here.

1062
01:13:00,368 --> 01:13:01,942
I wish I could.

1063
01:13:02,184 --> 01:13:04,765
As a species, we're fundamentally insane.

1064
01:13:05,360 --> 01:13:07,154
Put more than two of us in a room,

1065
01:13:07,179 --> 01:13:10,306
we pick sides and start dreaming up reasons
to kill one another.

1066
01:13:11,512 --> 01:13:13,913
Why do you think we invented
politics and religion?

1067
01:13:13,931 --> 01:13:17,606
Oh, Jesus, that's just... wrong.

1068
01:13:17,631 --> 01:13:20,108
Look, nobody has to decide anything now,
okay?

1069
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:21,822
First things first,

1070
01:13:22,424 --> 01:13:23,571
the pharmacy.

1071
01:13:24,823 --> 01:13:27,547
That'll be our test run. Okay?

1072
01:13:37,968 --> 01:13:41,382
It's all right, Big Bill. I'm gonna
bring you back some comic books.

1073
01:13:41,407 --> 01:13:42,738
I don't want them.

1074
01:13:43,124 --> 01:13:44,780
I want you to stay here.

1075
01:13:45,066 --> 01:13:49,312
I won't be gone long.
Just... Just next door.

1076
01:13:49,822 --> 01:13:52,155
Hey, you'll be safe.

1077
01:13:53,405 --> 01:13:54,341
Daddy...

1078
01:13:54,366 --> 01:13:57,960
Daddy, there are things out there.
Things...

1079
01:13:58,657 --> 01:14:01,991
Yeah. There's a lot less of 'em 
in the daytime.

1080
01:14:03,180 --> 01:14:04,343
They'll wait.

1081
01:14:04,649 --> 01:14:06,060
They'll wait in the mist
where you can't see 'em,

1082
01:14:06,085 --> 01:14:09,957
and then when you go and can't get back in,
they'll come and eat you up!

1083
01:14:09,982 --> 01:14:11,210
Shh.

1084
01:14:11,235 --> 01:14:12,530
Daddy, don't go!

1085
01:14:21,889 --> 01:14:23,218
I'll be back.

1086
01:14:24,460 --> 01:14:26,758
Big Bill... I promise.

1087
01:14:27,366 --> 01:14:31,624
I'll be back, and then 
I'm gonna take you home. All right?

1088
01:14:32,034 --> 01:14:34,327
Together, we're going home.

1089
01:14:35,137 --> 01:14:38,228
If something happens,
anything at all, you cut and run.

1090
01:14:38,421 --> 01:14:41,194
You get your ass back in here,
for your boy's sake.

1091
01:14:41,310 --> 01:14:46,007
If something happens to me, I want you
to take care of Billy best as you can,

1092
01:14:46,032 --> 01:14:47,593
and long as you can.

1093
01:14:48,064 --> 01:14:49,913
Land Cruiser's yours now.

1094
01:14:50,277 --> 01:14:52,034
You... You get him out of here.

1095
01:14:52,044 --> 01:14:53,546
You just keep drivin'.

1096
01:15:00,162 --> 01:15:02,302
Where do you think you're going,
Mr. David Drayton?

1097
01:15:02,327 --> 01:15:05,099
Are you so anxious to make your boy 
an orphan?

1098
01:15:05,124 --> 01:15:07,217
My boy is no concern of yours.

1099
01:15:07,507 --> 01:15:08,602
Listen up.

1100
01:15:09,059 --> 01:15:10,833
We're going to the pharmacy.

1101
01:15:11,132 --> 01:15:12,894
We're gonna bring back some supplies.

1102
01:15:12,919 --> 01:15:16,247
Also, there may be people
trapped over there who need help.

1103
01:15:16,762 --> 01:15:18,581
Listen, folks, listen!

1104
01:15:18,606 --> 01:15:20,534
We're not gonna take any chances.

1105
01:15:20,558 --> 01:15:24,191
If there's any trouble, we'll come
straight back here to the supermarket.

1106
01:15:24,223 --> 01:15:27,836
And bring the fiends of hell
down on our heads, thank you.

1107
01:15:27,861 --> 01:15:32,614
She's right. You'll make 'em notice us.
You'll make 'em come.

1108
01:15:33,232 --> 01:15:35,928
Why can't you just leave well enough alone?

1109
01:15:35,948 --> 01:15:38,121
Lady, this what you call 'well enough"?

1110
01:15:38,146 --> 01:15:39,636
You wanna stop us?

1111
01:15:39,872 --> 01:15:40,934
You better explain to Bobby here

1112
01:15:40,959 --> 01:15:43,464
why we're not bringin' painkillers
and medicine back for his brother.

1113
01:15:43,489 --> 01:15:45,863
I'm goin', even if I have to go alone.

1114
01:15:45,875 --> 01:15:47,605
You'll die out there, young man.

1115
01:15:47,630 --> 01:15:50,444
You'll walk out that door
and be torn to shreds,

1116
01:15:50,463 --> 01:15:53,808
and then your hell-bound pride
will have them come get the rest of us.

1117
01:15:53,841 --> 01:15:57,057
Yes, they'll come back for all of us,
just like this good lady said.

1118
01:15:57,067 --> 01:15:59,673
- Do you want that to happen, people?
- No!

1119
01:15:59,697 --> 01:16:02,204
No! No! No!

1120
01:16:02,229 --> 01:16:04,069
Well, it is this kind of hubris

1121
01:16:04,093 --> 01:16:06,527
that brought the wrath of God
in the first place.

1122
01:16:06,552 --> 01:16:08,442
This kind of pride and defiance of-

1123
01:16:09,724 --> 01:16:11,765
Shut up, you miserable buzzard!

1124
01:16:11,790 --> 01:16:13,208
You old bitch!

1125
01:16:17,246 --> 01:16:20,340
Stoning people who piss you off
is perfectly okay.

1126
01:16:20,367 --> 01:16:22,487
They do it in the Bible, don't they?

1127
01:16:22,512 --> 01:16:23,977
And I got lots of peas.

1128
01:16:24,002 --> 01:16:26,596
David, please, if you want to go,
now's the time.

1129
01:16:27,067 --> 01:16:30,083
How 'bout it, Army?
Any help from the armed forces?

1130
01:16:30,252 --> 01:16:31,520
I'll go.

1131
01:16:33,839 --> 01:16:36,816
Jim Grondin. I had you in school, didn't I?

1132
01:16:36,841 --> 01:16:38,786
Yes, me and my sister Pauline.

1133
01:16:38,886 --> 01:16:40,758
Pair of underachievers.

1134
01:16:40,783 --> 01:16:42,011
After you, Jim.

1135
01:16:42,794 --> 01:16:44,130
Yes, ma'am.

1136
01:16:44,155 --> 01:16:45,486
Oh, shit.

1137
01:16:45,511 --> 01:16:49,570
That it? That's everybody?
Everybody that's goin'.

1138
01:16:49,595 --> 01:16:50,692
Yep.

1139
01:16:51,028 --> 01:16:52,005
Okay.

1140
01:16:52,012 --> 01:16:56,684
Single file, one by one, all right?
Let's get this thing over with.

1141
01:16:57,865 --> 01:16:58,854
Let's go.

1142
01:16:58,879 --> 01:17:00,981
- After you.
- Yes.

1143
01:17:03,829 --> 01:17:04,981
Stay together.

1144
01:17:08,362 --> 01:17:09,637
You know what?

1145
01:17:09,794 --> 01:17:11,453
Mrs. Carmody, you're not helping.

1146
01:17:11,462 --> 01:17:13,316
- Shut the hell up!
- You shut up!

1147
01:17:19,946 --> 01:17:21,489
Save the batteries.

1148
01:18:08,720 --> 01:18:12,492
Shit. They left the doors propped open.

1149
01:18:13,729 --> 01:18:15,403
Think something got in?

1150
01:18:16,986 --> 01:18:21,161
Let's just... get what we need,
get the hell outta here.

1151
01:18:21,186 --> 01:18:22,862
Yeah. Let's do that.

1152
01:18:22,887 --> 01:18:27,248
The meds are over at the end there,
in the cubicle.

1153
01:18:47,848 --> 01:18:51,091
- Will you not do that?
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1154
01:18:51,272 --> 01:18:52,971
Oh, God.

1155
01:19:17,937 --> 01:19:19,151
Where's that Silvadene?

1156
01:19:19,511 --> 01:19:22,857
It's over behind David.
In the fridge. Check there.

1157
01:19:28,720 --> 01:19:30,336
Silvadene. Got it.

1158
01:19:30,774 --> 01:19:32,833
- Good.
- Ollie, what are we lookin' for?

1159
01:19:32,858 --> 01:19:34,639
- Penicillin.
- Yeah.

1160
01:19:34,664 --> 01:19:37,258
- Any strong antibiotics.
- Yeah.

1161
01:19:37,856 --> 01:19:41,198
Pain meds like Vicodin or OxyContin.

1162
01:19:41,233 --> 01:19:42,812
- Shh!
- OxyContin!

1163
01:19:44,515 --> 01:19:46,445
Hydrochloride?

1164
01:19:48,740 --> 01:19:49,729
Penicillin.

1165
01:20:01,636 --> 01:20:02,625
Guys.

1166
01:20:06,056 --> 01:20:07,797
Hurry it up. I hear something.

1167
01:20:11,693 --> 01:20:12,695
What?

1168
01:20:14,898 --> 01:20:16,844
Somethin' fuckin' weird.

1169
01:20:26,117 --> 01:20:27,523
Oh, God.

1170
01:20:27,961 --> 01:20:29,148
Oh, God!

1171
01:20:29,625 --> 01:20:33,134
No. Oh, no.

1172
01:20:33,648 --> 01:20:35,022
Oh, no...

1173
01:20:35,047 --> 01:20:36,789
Oh, fuck.

1174
01:20:38,248 --> 01:20:40,494
Look. There's another one.

1175
01:20:40,519 --> 01:20:43,283
- Oh, my God.
- No, no, no.

1176
01:20:43,355 --> 01:20:45,721
Oh, no, no.

1177
01:20:46,314 --> 01:20:49,477
Guys, let's get out of here now.

1178
01:20:51,911 --> 01:20:53,461
Holy shit!

1179
01:20:56,368 --> 01:20:58,726
Shit! Shit! Oh, shit!

1180
01:20:59,646 --> 01:21:03,655
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! Help me!

1181
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:05,625
Good Lord! Help him!

1182
01:21:11,955 --> 01:21:14,982
Son of a bitch! 
This stuff ain't comin' off!

1183
01:21:15,571 --> 01:21:18,255
Oh, man!
He's glued to this fuckin' post!

1184
01:21:18,280 --> 01:21:22,017
It's our fault. It's all our fault.

1185
01:21:22,273 --> 01:21:23,763
It's really stuck.

1186
01:21:27,971 --> 01:21:29,962
God, I can feel 'em!

1187
01:21:30,365 --> 01:21:31,962
I can feel 'em!

1188
01:21:33,818 --> 01:21:35,752
Oh, my God! Jesus!

1189
01:21:42,971 --> 01:21:44,358
Oh, my God.

1190
01:21:44,842 --> 01:21:46,682
Oh! I...

1191
01:21:57,164 --> 01:21:58,523
There's more!

1192
01:22:08,303 --> 01:22:09,633
There's another one! Hit it!

1193
01:22:11,563 --> 01:22:13,398
What the hell is that stuff?

1194
01:22:13,969 --> 01:22:15,543
Ollie! One over there!

1195
01:22:15,883 --> 01:22:17,257
Ollie, there!

1196
01:22:17,282 --> 01:22:18,328
Got it!

1197
01:22:19,050 --> 01:22:21,281
There, there, there!
Shoot! Shoot!

1198
01:22:22,187 --> 01:22:23,375
Shit!

1199
01:22:25,640 --> 01:22:26,781
See 'em?

1200
01:22:30,078 --> 01:22:31,271
Bobby!

1201
01:22:31,296 --> 01:22:32,539
Bobby!

1202
01:22:38,648 --> 01:22:40,514
Hold on, man! Hold on!

1203
01:22:40,953 --> 01:22:42,315
- Hold on, man!
- Cut the strand!

1204
01:22:42,785 --> 01:22:43,774
Help me!

1205
01:22:44,644 --> 01:22:45,883
Let's get out of here!

1206
01:22:48,655 --> 01:22:51,021
- A belt! Who's got a belt?
- I got a belt!

1207
01:22:56,037 --> 01:22:57,625
- I got him, I got him.
- Hold on.

1208
01:22:58,323 --> 01:22:59,398
Pull it tight!

1209
01:23:01,481 --> 01:23:03,108
Look! Look!

1210
01:23:11,130 --> 01:23:12,138
Light!

1211
01:23:12,646 --> 01:23:13,447
Light!

1212
01:23:15,310 --> 01:23:16,115
God!

1213
01:23:19,396 --> 01:23:21,865
We gotta get outta here! Come on!

1214
01:23:22,550 --> 01:23:24,818
Let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go, let's go!

1215
01:23:25,826 --> 01:23:27,240
Watch it, watch it, watch it!

1216
01:23:38,711 --> 01:23:40,144
Let's get out of here!

1217
01:23:40,738 --> 01:23:43,730
All right, go, go, go, go, go, go!
Come on!

1218
01:23:44,211 --> 01:23:45,371
Come on!

1219
01:23:52,454 --> 01:23:53,696
Oh, my God!

1220
01:23:55,907 --> 01:23:57,568
Ollie! Ollie!

1221
01:24:02,226 --> 01:24:03,758
Kill it! Kill it!

1222
01:24:14,758 --> 01:24:15,639
Fuckers!

1223
01:24:15,634 --> 01:24:16,807
Oh, no! Oh, God, he's dead!

1224
01:24:16,832 --> 01:24:19,686
He's dead! Get out of here!
Let's go, let's go!

1225
01:24:19,721 --> 01:24:21,657
Drayton, come on, come on, come on!

1226
01:24:21,682 --> 01:24:24,189
Come on, Drayton, he's dead! Come on!

1227
01:24:55,393 --> 01:24:56,724
Open the door!

1228
01:24:58,459 --> 01:24:59,653
Where's Bobby?

1229
01:24:59,678 --> 01:25:00,774
Daddy!

1230
01:25:02,014 --> 01:25:04,104
- Close up the doors!
- Hurry up!

1231
01:25:04,516 --> 01:25:06,106
What happened?

1232
01:25:06,140 --> 01:25:08,870
They're dead! They're all dead!

1233
01:25:25,662 --> 01:25:30,356
...because we have seen the earth
scourged with whips and scorpions.

1234
01:25:30,375 --> 01:25:35,295
We have seen the earth vomit forth
from her lips obscenities

1235
01:25:35,297 --> 01:25:39,139
and profanities of 
such nightmare proportions.

1236
01:25:39,134 --> 01:25:44,856
And for these evil, lurking spirits,
and for these evil people...

1237
01:25:44,890 --> 01:25:46,396
How long was I out?

1238
01:25:46,416 --> 01:25:47,815
Most of the day.

1239
01:25:48,781 --> 01:25:51,455
You just came over here to lay down
and went to sleep.

1240
01:25:51,480 --> 01:25:57,753
Just passed out, is more like it.
Just shut down for a while. Sorry.

1241
01:25:57,778 --> 01:25:59,066
How will it end?

1242
01:25:59,091 --> 01:26:00,080
Expiation!

1243
01:26:00,105 --> 01:26:02,733
Expiation!
Do you remember yesterday when...

1244
01:26:02,758 --> 01:26:04,217
How's Joe?

1245
01:26:04,693 --> 01:26:08,094
Dead. Joe died of his burns
while you were asleep.

1246
01:26:08,849 --> 01:26:10,423
We were just too late.

1247
01:26:10,448 --> 01:26:12,230
I told you this would come!

1248
01:26:12,255 --> 01:26:14,569
Oh, God,
I thought I was dreaming her voice.

1249
01:26:14,594 --> 01:26:15,695
No dream.

1250
01:26:16,180 --> 01:26:18,180
She's getting people whipped up.

1251
01:26:18,679 --> 01:26:23,237
That poor girl is dead,
and that boy is burnt in the back room!

1252
01:26:23,261 --> 01:26:27,366
She's got 'em believing she's a psychic,
she has a direct line with God.

1253
01:26:27,391 --> 01:26:29,776
Why wouldn't they?
Woman never shuts up.

1254
01:26:30,152 --> 01:26:32,430
Like those speeches Castro used to make.

1255
01:26:35,641 --> 01:26:38,184
Ollie says you're thinking of leaving.

1256
01:26:38,534 --> 01:26:39,628
I'm in.

1257
01:26:39,653 --> 01:26:41,621
No. Sorry.

1258
01:26:41,961 --> 01:26:45,592
I mean, come on, you saw 
what happened to Bobby... Mike...

1259
01:26:45,617 --> 01:26:49,376
I won't... do that again.
I won't be responsible.

1260
01:26:49,430 --> 01:26:50,897
You might want to reconsider that.

1261
01:26:50,922 --> 01:26:54,319
What will... What will keep these evil,
these abominations at bay?

1262
01:26:54,345 --> 01:26:55,935
What will keep them away?

1263
01:26:55,960 --> 01:26:59,049
"The rock will not hide them.
The dead tree gives no shelter."

1264
01:26:59,089 --> 01:27:00,617
What will end it? Let me hear it.

1265
01:27:00,642 --> 01:27:02,542
- Expiation!
- What are we talking about?

1266
01:27:02,567 --> 01:27:05,157
- Expiation!
- Say it again like you mean it!

1267
01:27:05,182 --> 01:27:06,967
Expiation!

1268
01:27:07,192 --> 01:27:11,551
Welcome to Sesame Street.
Today's word is "expiation".

1269
01:27:11,576 --> 01:27:13,824
Hallelujah! Hallelujah!

1270
01:27:13,849 --> 01:27:16,553
That boy hasn't been right 
since the pharmacy.

1271
01:27:17,240 --> 01:27:19,459
His mind's just snapped. Gone.

1272
01:27:19,484 --> 01:27:21,506
Hasn't even been two days.

1273
01:27:22,140 --> 01:27:23,903
Not even two days.

1274
01:27:23,928 --> 01:27:26,678
I'm not spendin' the rest of my life here,
I'll tell you what.

1275
01:27:26,873 --> 01:27:29,262
I can quietly gather up
some bags of groceries

1276
01:27:29,287 --> 01:27:32,485
and hide them up at one of
the check stands by the door.

1277
01:27:32,510 --> 01:27:34,774
It was your idea. It's your vehicle.

1278
01:27:35,001 --> 01:27:36,491
It'll be your call.

1279
01:27:37,995 --> 01:27:40,670
I'd rather die out there trying
than in here waiting.

1280
01:27:43,175 --> 01:27:48,421
Who will save them? No one.
The rocks will not hide them.

1281
01:27:48,764 --> 01:27:53,576
I want some idea of what we're up
against. I want to know what this mist is.

1282
01:27:54,311 --> 01:27:57,301
- I want to talk to the soldiers.
- Soldiers? What's that gonna do?

1283
01:27:57,314 --> 01:27:59,559
You heard what that M.P. said
at the pharmacy.

1284
01:27:59,584 --> 01:28:03,503
David, I'm not even sure I knew 
he was talking. The situation was insane.

1285
01:28:03,528 --> 01:28:07,621
He said he was sorry. Wasn't
that the word he used..."sorry"?

1286
01:28:07,646 --> 01:28:09,981
That's right.
He said it was their fault, right?

1287
01:28:10,006 --> 01:28:11,582
What did he mean by that?

1288
01:28:11,607 --> 01:28:13,660
That's what we're gonna find out.

1289
01:28:13,787 --> 01:28:15,448
Irene, stay with Billy, please.

1290
01:28:15,607 --> 01:28:16,816
Verse 17!

1291
01:28:17,172 --> 01:28:21,348
"...poured out his vial into the air,
and there came a great voice

1292
01:28:21,373 --> 01:28:24,639
"out of the temple of heaven
from the throne, saying,

1293
01:28:24,716 --> 01:28:26,974
"'It is done! It is done! '

1294
01:28:26,982 --> 01:28:30,029
"And there were voices and lightning,

1295
01:28:30,054 --> 01:28:32,576
and thunders, and a great earthquake."

1296
01:28:33,412 --> 01:28:35,326
Yes! Come to me!

1297
01:28:35,977 --> 01:28:37,137
What?

1298
01:28:37,389 --> 01:28:39,615
- Where's your friends?
- I ain't seen 'em.

1299
01:28:39,849 --> 01:28:41,775
Not that big a store. 
It's kinda hard to lose.

1300
01:28:41,800 --> 01:28:44,920
I ain't seen 'em, I said.
I look like their keeper?

1301
01:28:48,114 --> 01:28:49,479
What do you want from me?

1302
01:28:49,503 --> 01:28:51,176
What do you know about this mist?

1303
01:28:51,201 --> 01:28:53,533
I don't know nothin'.
I got nothin' to do with it.

1304
01:28:53,558 --> 01:28:55,321
That's not what the M.P.
said in the pharmacy

1305
01:28:55,346 --> 01:28:57,646
before the spiders
came out of his skin.

1306
01:28:58,716 --> 01:29:00,479
They're not in the store.

1307
01:29:00,826 --> 01:29:03,753
The only place we haven't looked
is the loading dock.

1308
01:29:03,838 --> 01:29:07,215
...because you know.
You saw the good face of God tonight.

1309
01:29:07,240 --> 01:29:08,652
Yes? Tell us.

1310
01:29:08,677 --> 01:29:10,642
Here is an old man who has seen!

1311
01:29:10,818 --> 01:29:12,939
Yes, he has seen!

1312
01:29:12,964 --> 01:29:13,953
Amen.

1313
01:29:14,185 --> 01:29:20,631
And I want to say, do I want to walk
with you into my Father's hands?

1314
01:29:21,336 --> 01:29:22,451
Morales.

1315
01:29:23,238 --> 01:29:24,474
Donaldson.

1316
01:29:27,056 --> 01:29:28,240
Guys...

1317
01:29:30,252 --> 01:29:32,029
It's the only place they can be.

1318
01:29:32,771 --> 01:29:33,660
What?

1319
01:29:33,685 --> 01:29:35,162
Couldn't just disappear.

1320
01:29:35,187 --> 01:29:38,179
Look, I told you, okay, 
I don't know where they are...

1321
01:29:45,367 --> 01:29:49,498
I didn't think they'd do it.
They said they would do it, and I just...

1322
01:29:49,598 --> 01:29:52,885
I told them what the M.P. said at 
the pharmacy, and they swore they'd do it.

1323
01:29:52,910 --> 01:29:55,715
I just... I didn't think they would.
Oh, Jesus.

1324
01:29:55,724 --> 01:29:59,024
It's the Arrowhead Project, isn't it?

1325
01:29:59,060 --> 01:30:02,655
This mist, it's some kind of, what,
military fuckup?

1326
01:30:02,680 --> 01:30:04,267
What were you guys
messin' with up there, huh?

1327
01:30:04,292 --> 01:30:07,159
We got you now, you sorry son of a bitch!

1328
01:30:07,184 --> 01:30:08,280
Get in there!

1329
01:30:08,305 --> 01:30:11,297
It was them!
It was them what done it to us!

1330
01:30:11,322 --> 01:30:14,951
It was them what brung down
the final wrath upon us!

1331
01:30:15,131 --> 01:30:17,676
Those two peckerwoods that
he's been with this whole time,

1332
01:30:17,701 --> 01:30:21,421
they hung themselves in the back
because they knew! They knew it all along!

1333
01:30:21,458 --> 01:30:23,421
- He's crazy. He doesn't know-
- Get on your knees!

1334
01:30:23,446 --> 01:30:24,777
Stay out of it, Drayton!

1335
01:30:24,794 --> 01:30:26,969
They heard it too, didn't you? All of ya!

1336
01:30:27,005 --> 01:30:30,564
All about the Arrowhead Project and
all that secret shit up on the mountain.

1337
01:30:30,589 --> 01:30:34,395
That's what brung it down on us.
That's what brung down the wrath of God!

1338
01:30:34,420 --> 01:30:35,409
Oh!

1339
01:30:37,230 --> 01:30:38,948
Private Jessup.

1340
01:30:40,899 --> 01:30:45,899
It wasn't me. I'm just... I'm stationed
up there. I'm not responsible...

1341
01:30:45,899 --> 01:30:48,048
- Bullshit!
- Hell, I'm a local!

1342
01:30:48,073 --> 01:30:50,003
Most of you people know me.

1343
01:30:50,028 --> 01:30:55,122
You stop your chicken shit whining
or I will cut your puling tongue out.

1344
01:30:55,163 --> 01:30:56,795
Now you tell us!

1345
01:30:58,823 --> 01:30:59,920
Tell us.

1346
01:31:00,246 --> 01:31:04,256
Look, look. Okay, okay.
I heard stuff.

1347
01:31:04,269 --> 01:31:05,418
Stuff?

1348
01:31:05,443 --> 01:31:07,654
Yes, we all heard stuff.

1349
01:31:09,263 --> 01:31:15,025
Like how they, um, how they thought
that there were other dimensions,

1350
01:31:15,050 --> 01:31:17,664
you know, other...
other worlds all around us,

1351
01:31:17,689 --> 01:31:22,277
and how they wanted to try and make, um,
a window,

1352
01:31:22,302 --> 01:31:24,896
you know, so they could look through
and see what's on the other side.

1353
01:31:26,734 --> 01:31:29,464
Well, maybe your window
turned out to be a door. Didn't it?

1354
01:31:29,489 --> 01:31:31,354
Not mine! Those scientists!

1355
01:31:31,369 --> 01:31:33,894
Oh, the scientists! Yes, the scientists!

1356
01:31:33,905 --> 01:31:36,195
They must have ripped
a hole open by accident.

1357
01:31:36,220 --> 01:31:38,303
This other world
came spilling through to ours.

1358
01:31:38,560 --> 01:31:41,593
That's what Donaldson was saying to me
right before he killed himself.

1359
01:31:41,618 --> 01:31:43,609
I didn't understand the half of it.

1360
01:31:45,722 --> 01:31:47,123
It ain't my fault!

1361
01:31:47,148 --> 01:31:48,206
Oh.

1362
01:31:49,162 --> 01:31:52,771
Ain't. His. Fault.

1363
01:31:53,448 --> 01:31:54,842
No, no, no.

1364
01:31:55,599 --> 01:31:59,420
Ain't nothin' ever anybody's fault.

1365
01:31:59,698 --> 01:32:01,896
But he denies it.

1366
01:32:02,181 --> 01:32:07,456
He points the finger,
this Judas in our midst.

1367
01:32:07,777 --> 01:32:08,770
Judas!

1368
01:32:08,795 --> 01:32:09,979
David!

1369
01:32:10,306 --> 01:32:12,536
You! You!

1370
01:32:13,042 --> 01:32:14,886
Don't you know by now?

1371
01:32:15,144 --> 01:32:16,856
Don't you know the truth?

1372
01:32:17,246 --> 01:32:19,452
We are being punished.

1373
01:32:19,477 --> 01:32:23,322
For what? 
For going against the will of God!

1374
01:32:23,347 --> 01:32:27,452
For going against
his forbidden rules of old!

1375
01:32:27,477 --> 01:32:29,333
Walking on the moon!

1376
01:32:29,358 --> 01:32:30,927
Yes! Yes!

1377
01:32:30,952 --> 01:32:33,606
- Or... or splitting his atoms!
- Amen!

1378
01:32:33,631 --> 01:32:38,364
Or... or... or stem cells and abortions!

1379
01:32:38,642 --> 01:32:44,491
And destroying the secrets of life
that only God above has any right to!

1380
01:32:44,517 --> 01:32:46,358
Amen! Amen!

1381
01:32:46,592 --> 01:32:48,988
Yes, I know! It is true!

1382
01:32:49,319 --> 01:32:54,627
And now we are being punished.
The judgment is being brought down upon us.

1383
01:32:54,652 --> 01:33:01,208
The fiends of hell, you see they are
let loose, and star Wormwood blazes!

1384
01:33:01,233 --> 01:33:02,435
And it is his fault!

1385
01:33:02,460 --> 01:33:05,793
No! No! It is not my fault! No!

1386
01:33:05,818 --> 01:33:08,908
They did it! 
They spit in the eye of the Almighty!

1387
01:33:08,933 --> 01:33:09,922
No!

1388
01:33:11,403 --> 01:33:12,601
Get over there!

1389
01:33:13,254 --> 01:33:14,208
No!

1390
01:33:14,412 --> 01:33:15,565
Judas!

1391
01:33:17,280 --> 01:33:18,122
Jim!

1392
01:33:18,147 --> 01:33:20,410
Kill him! String him up!

1393
01:33:23,481 --> 01:33:25,142
Stand up, you coward!

1394
01:33:30,227 --> 01:33:31,387
Jesus!

1395
01:33:34,381 --> 01:33:35,301
No!

1396
01:33:36,614 --> 01:33:38,356
Expiation!

1397
01:33:39,363 --> 01:33:40,455
- No!
- Stab him!

1398
01:33:43,083 --> 01:33:44,333
Expiation!

1399
01:33:44,825 --> 01:33:47,042
Feed him to the beast!

1400
01:33:47,067 --> 01:33:48,772
Expiation!

1401
01:33:48,840 --> 01:33:52,799
Let the abominations smell his blood!

1402
01:33:54,312 --> 01:33:55,973
No, no! No!

1403
01:33:58,716 --> 01:34:00,571
Jesus! Wait!

1404
01:34:00,596 --> 01:34:02,154
No, David!

1405
01:34:59,005 --> 01:35:00,309
Please.

1406
01:35:10,755 --> 01:35:13,565
The beast will leave us alone tonight.

1407
01:35:15,199 --> 01:35:16,188
Tomorrow...

1408
01:35:17,467 --> 01:35:20,291
Tomorrow, we'll just have to wait and see.

1409
01:35:29,466 --> 01:35:30,626
Daddy.

1410
01:35:32,114 --> 01:35:33,274
Daddy.

1411
01:35:44,916 --> 01:35:46,747
Sorry I left you, pal.

1412
01:35:49,385 --> 01:35:51,241
I'll never leave you again.

1413
01:35:52,449 --> 01:35:53,609
Promise?

1414
01:35:54,747 --> 01:35:58,444
But you have to give me
your best promise, okay?

1415
01:35:58,469 --> 01:36:01,905
Your very best promise,
and can never break it.

1416
01:36:02,144 --> 01:36:03,468
Tell me.

1417
01:36:05,409 --> 01:36:07,952
Promise you won't let the monsters get me.

1418
01:36:11,555 --> 01:36:13,913
Ever. No matter what.

1419
01:36:15,831 --> 01:36:17,304
I promise.

1420
01:36:20,749 --> 01:36:22,335
I love you, Daddy.

1421
01:36:22,485 --> 01:36:24,069
I love you, Billy.

1422
01:36:25,207 --> 01:36:26,538
More than anything.

1423
01:36:55,918 --> 01:36:57,460
It's dawn.

1424
01:37:02,561 --> 01:37:05,278
Hey, pal, you ready to go home?

1425
01:37:05,935 --> 01:37:07,300
Come on.

1426
01:37:09,327 --> 01:37:12,318
Okay, I got the groceries
hidden at check stand number two.

1427
01:37:12,343 --> 01:37:14,687
Five bags. We can grab 'em
and get out the door.

1428
01:37:15,156 --> 01:37:16,103
Okay.

1429
01:37:16,671 --> 01:37:19,859
My car's parked in the center lane
of the parking lot, far end.

1430
01:37:20,085 --> 01:37:22,794
Whoever gets there first,
open up both doors,

1431
01:37:22,819 --> 01:37:24,864
and we'll all pile in as
fast as we can, okay?

1432
01:37:24,889 --> 01:37:26,049
Let's go.

1433
01:37:49,681 --> 01:37:51,876
Stealing food now?

1434
01:37:56,482 --> 01:37:58,473
Going out now, Mrs. Carmody.

1435
01:37:59,974 --> 01:38:01,635
Please stand aside.

1436
01:38:02,513 --> 01:38:05,052
You can't go out. I won't allow it.

1437
01:38:05,170 --> 01:38:06,305
Won't allow it?

1438
01:38:06,330 --> 01:38:11,193
It's against God's will.
Don't you know that by now?

1439
01:38:11,566 --> 01:38:15,881
Haven't I proven myself
again and again and again?

1440
01:38:16,577 --> 01:38:20,647
Haven't I shown that I am his vessel?

1441
01:38:25,249 --> 01:38:27,140
What's the matter with you?

1442
01:38:30,290 --> 01:38:31,999
Don't you believe in God?

1443
01:38:32,405 --> 01:38:34,132
No one's interfered with you.

1444
01:38:34,812 --> 01:38:36,890
All we're asking for
is the same privilege.

1445
01:38:37,124 --> 01:38:38,455
You heard him.

1446
01:38:40,037 --> 01:38:44,303
It is these people
who brought this upon us.

1447
01:38:45,328 --> 01:38:50,082
They... people who refused
to bend to the will of God,

1448
01:38:50,107 --> 01:38:52,701
and claim it privilege.

1449
01:38:53,060 --> 01:38:55,821
Sinners in pride.

1450
01:38:56,318 --> 01:38:58,058
Yes, haughty.

1451
01:38:58,329 --> 01:38:59,956
Privileged!

1452
01:39:00,184 --> 01:39:04,184
They mock us. They mock our...
our God, our faith,

1453
01:39:04,209 --> 01:39:07,542
our values, our very lifestyle.

1454
01:39:07,567 --> 01:39:14,758
They mock our humility and our
piousness. They piss on us and laugh.

1455
01:39:18,083 --> 01:39:23,306
It's from them the blood of
human sacrifice must come.

1456
01:39:23,884 --> 01:39:25,351
From them...

1457
01:39:25,955 --> 01:39:28,020
- Come on.
...the blood of expiation.

1458
01:39:28,045 --> 01:39:29,034
Come on.

1459
01:39:29,790 --> 01:39:30,821
You try it.

1460
01:39:31,001 --> 01:39:32,415
Fuckin' try it!

1461
01:39:32,610 --> 01:39:33,659
Come on!

1462
01:39:34,218 --> 01:39:35,976
We want the boy.

1463
01:39:35,970 --> 01:39:37,396
- We want the boy!
- You get back!

1464
01:39:38,395 --> 01:39:39,562
You get back!

1465
01:39:39,590 --> 01:39:40,734
The boy!

1466
01:39:42,092 --> 01:39:43,957
Grab that boy! Grab him!

1467
01:39:47,998 --> 01:39:49,329
Grab him!

1468
01:39:51,187 --> 01:39:52,845
And get the whore too!

1469
01:39:53,046 --> 01:39:54,280
Grab her!

1470
01:39:54,624 --> 01:39:56,839
Kill 'em! Kill 'em all!

1471
01:40:12,304 --> 01:40:13,749
Stay down! Stay down! Stay down!

1472
01:40:20,732 --> 01:40:22,747
I... I killed her.

1473
01:40:24,640 --> 01:40:25,919
Thank you, Ollie.

1474
01:40:27,802 --> 01:40:29,052
Let's go.

1475
01:40:30,388 --> 01:40:33,247
Get that ice machine
out of the way, please.

1476
01:40:35,655 --> 01:40:37,621
You killed her!

1477
01:40:37,646 --> 01:40:39,978
You murdered her!

1478
01:40:43,537 --> 01:40:46,797
I wouldn't have shot her, Dave,
not if there'd been any other way.

1479
01:40:46,827 --> 01:40:48,396
That's why I said thank you.

1480
01:40:48,465 --> 01:40:49,577
Okay.

1481
01:40:49,602 --> 01:40:51,934
Okay, then... let's go!

1482
01:40:53,697 --> 01:40:54,788
Get up, Myron!

1483
01:40:54,813 --> 01:40:56,075
Come on! We gotta go!

1484
01:40:56,100 --> 01:40:57,263
My ankle!

1485
01:41:05,717 --> 01:41:08,049
Okay. All the way down!

1486
01:41:09,159 --> 01:41:10,422
Where are they?

1487
01:41:10,620 --> 01:41:12,376
Bud! Myron!

1488
01:41:12,401 --> 01:41:13,425
Ambrose!

1489
01:41:13,450 --> 01:41:15,042
I think I broke it!

1490
01:41:15,171 --> 01:41:16,729
Come on! Come on!

1491
01:41:16,754 --> 01:41:18,297
We gotta go! Come on, come on!

1492
01:41:18,322 --> 01:41:19,550
They're lost!

1493
01:41:27,862 --> 01:41:28,941
- Oh, Jesus.
- Ollie!

1494
01:41:29,659 --> 01:41:30,893
Ollie!

1495
01:42:11,275 --> 01:42:12,877
All that screaming!

1496
01:42:13,831 --> 01:42:16,010
Are they out there? Can they see us?

1497
01:42:26,182 --> 01:42:28,690
Let me... let me in! Let me in!

1498
01:42:42,993 --> 01:42:44,483
Are we going?

1499
01:42:51,521 --> 01:42:52,458
- No.
- Yeah.

1500
01:42:52,483 --> 01:42:54,576
- No! No!
- Yeah!

1501
01:42:54,857 --> 01:42:56,162
- Daddy.
- David.

1502
01:42:56,404 --> 01:42:58,030
- David, no.
- Daddy, no.

1503
01:42:58,443 --> 01:42:59,818
